<p><b>You find the manual page for the container configuration file <a href="https://linuxcontainers.org/lxc/manpages/man5/lxc.container.conf.5.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">here</a>!</p></b>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><b>These commands are used if you want to interact with LXC from the terminal:</b></p>
<p><b>To attach to a started container type in:</b></br><code>lxc-attach CONTAINERNAME /bin/bash</code><br /><em>(please replace /bin/bash with the corresponding shell)</em></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>To start a container enter:<br /><code>lxc-start CONTAINERNAME</code></p>
<p>To stop a container enter:<br /><code>lxc-stop CONTAINERNAME</code><code></code></p>
<p>To kill a container enter:<br /><code>lxc-stop --kill CONTAINERNAME</code><code></code><code></code></p>
<p>To delete a container enter:<br /><code>lxc-destroy CONTAINERNAME</code><br /><em>(the container must be stopped in the first place)</em></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>To install Alpine Edge container manually open up a Terminal and enter:<br /><code>lxc-create --name Alpine --template download -- --dist alpine --release edge --arch amd64</code></p>
<p>To install Arch current container manually open up a Terminal and enter:<br /><code>lxc-create --name Arch --template download -- --dist archlinux --release current --arch amd64</code></p>
<p>To install CentOS 7 container manually open up a Terminal and enter:<br /><code>lxc-create --name CentOS --template download -- --dist centos --release 7 --arch amd64</code></p>
<p>To install a Debian Bullseye container manually open up a Terminal and enter:<br /><code>lxc-create --name Debian --template download -- --dist debian --release bullseye --arch amd64</code></p>
<p>To install Fedora 36 container manually open up a Terminal and enter:<br /><code>lxc-create --name Fedora --template download -- --dist fedora --release 36 --arch amd64</code></p>
<p>To install Ubuntu Xenial container manually open up a Terminal and enter:<br /><code>lxc-create --name Ubuntu --template download -- --dist ubuntu --release xenial --arch amd64</code></p>
